This document explains the **different types of AI agents**, how they work, and where they are used in **real-world Agentic AI systems**.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“Œ 1. What Are AI Agents?

An **AI Agent** is an entity that:

* Observes its environment
* Makes decisions
* Takes actions to achieve goals

Different agents are designed based on **complexity, memory, and intelligence**.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§© 2. Types of AI Agents

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 2.1 Simple Reflex Agent

âœ… How It Works

* Acts only on **current input**
* Uses **if-else rules**
* No memory

Example:

```text
If temperature > 30 â†’ Turn on AC
```

âŒ Limitations

* No learning
* No past awareness

ğŸ·ï¸ Use Case

* Simple automation systems

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 2.2 Model-Based Agent

âœ… How It Works

* Maintains **internal state**
* Uses a **model of the environment**
* Can handle partial information

Example:

```text
Remembers last room temperature before acting
```

ğŸ·ï¸ Use Case

* Navigation systems
* Game AI

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 2.3 Goal-Based Agent

âœ… How It Works

* Has a **goal**
* Plans actions to reach the goal
* Evaluates multiple possibilities

Example:

```text
Goal â†’ Reach destination using best route
```

ğŸ·ï¸ Use Case

* Path planning
* Task automation

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 2.4 Utility-Based Agent

âœ… How It Works

* Uses a **utility function**
* Chooses the action with **maximum benefit**
* Considers performance, cost, risk

Example:

```text
Choose fastest and cheapest option
```

ğŸ·ï¸ Use Case

* Recommendation systems
* Financial decision systems

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 2.5 Learning Agent

âœ… How It Works

* Learns from **experience**
* Improves performance over time
* Adapts to environment

Components:

* Learning element
* Performance element
* Critic
* Problem generator

ğŸ·ï¸ Use Case

* ML models
* Reinforcement learning systems

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 2.6 Multi-Agent Systems

âœ… How It Works

* Multiple agents work together
* Agents can **communicate**
* Tasks are divided among agents

Example:

```text
One agent researches
Another writes code
Another tests output
```

ğŸ·ï¸ Use Case

* CrewAI
* Swarm systems
* Distributed AI

